            <title>[CASSANDRA-3111] Bug in ReversedType comparator</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3111</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Scenario :&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;create a cf with a reversed comparator&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;insert a few columns in a row&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;try to read data with : SliceRange(start=&apos;&apos;, finish=&apos;&apos;, reversed=true)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;no data is returned, but some columns are expected&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;try to read data with : SliceRange(start=&apos;&apos;, finish=&apos;&apos;, reversed=false)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;if not flushed on disk : no data is returned&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


</description>
